cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with community detection in networks. It may also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it introduces a new method for quantifying network structure. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new algorithm for community detection. The paper also involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
